  "tips": [
    {
      "type": "lead",
      "text": "Newsroom speed is built on clean, repeatable motion - not panic. Loop each word until it runs itself, then carry that smoothness into real copy. Flow, not force."
    },
    {
      "type": "drop",
      "text": "Hands on home row, eyes off the keys. Repeat each word at one even pace - same gap between every tap. Don't push the speed, let the steady beat set it for you."
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "icon": "🎶",
      "title": "Even beat",
      "text": "Lock a tempo you can hold all the way through. Smooth and even beats fast and jerky every time - a steady hand files faster than a rushed one. Trust the rhythm."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "unit": "markets",
      "baseReps": 5,
      "keys": ["m", "a", "r", "k", "e", "t", "s"],
      "target": "markets markets markets markets markets",
      "finger": "blue",
      "title": "Rhythm: markets",
      "hint": "Loop it on the beat: markets - markets - markets. Same gap every time."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "unit": "cloud",
      "baseReps": 4,
      "keys": ["c", "l", "o", "u", "d"],
      "target": "cloud cloud cloud cloud",
      "finger": "green",
      "title": "Rhythm: cloud",
      "hint": "Hold the tempo: cloud - cloud - cloud. Flow, not force."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "unit": "growth",
      "baseReps": 4,
      "keys": ["g", "r", "o", "w", "t", "h"],
      "target": "growth growth growth growth",
      "finger": "blue",
      "title": "Rhythm: growth",
      "hint": "Stay even to the end: growth - growth - growth. Don't rush the finish."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "Feel the longer words flowing as one smooth move instead of a string of letters? That is the engine of speed - even reps turn effort into reflex, and reflex holds up under deadline."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "All three drills done? Hit \"Open trainer\" below and run the full lesson text in one go. That run saves to your progress and unlocks the next lesson."
